# Log Configuration Examples
# This file is automatically watched - changes take effect immediately!
# All non-comment, non-empty lines are concatenated together.

# Basic log levels (use one):
info
# debug
# trace
# warn
# error

# ===== ADVANCED EXAMPLES =====
# You can split complex filters across multiple lines for readability:

# Example 1: Debug for app, warn for MQTT library
# ezv2_t1=debug,
# rumqttc=warn

# Example 2: Info generally, but debug for SENSOR topic only
# info,
# ezv2_t1[{topic="tele/EZPlugV2_743EEC/SENSOR"}]=debug

# Example 3: Show only STATE topic messages
# ezv2_t1[{topic="tele/EZPlugV2_743EEC/STATE"}]=debug

# Example 4: Show only SENSOR topic messages
# ezv2_t1[{topic="tele/EZPlugV2_743EEC/SENSOR"}]=debug

# Example 5: Multi-line complex filter
# ezv2_t1=debug,
# rumqttc=warn,
# sqlx=warn
